# Agent comms gateway

An always-on gateway agent that fully replaces joelclaw messaging. All fleet agents talk to Joel through it. It owns the conversation surface in both directions: voice, formatting, system context, reply routing, reactions, and intent. It replaces deterministic routing (kinds tables, lanes, suppression) with judgment.

Inheritance: [charter context](../../tasks/grill-master-agent-comms-gateway-context.svx). Sibling effort: `messaging-stabilization` (priority-lane removal is implemented and awaiting steering). The resilience-engineering brief pinned this workload's shape: container service riding the bus and wake registry.

## Finish line

1. The kind→routing-table path is dead code. Every outbound message reaches Joel because the gateway agent decided to deliver it — content, timing, format, and platform are its call.
2. Every inbound message from Joel (reply, reaction, button, free text) is interpreted by the agent, and it routes the response to the correct target: a live herdr pane, a revived session, or a bus consumer.
3. `joelclaw notify send` still exists as the wire format for producers, but it feeds the agent, not a routing table. No producer changed its call site.
4. A kill test passes: stop the agent container, send an alert-class message, and the fallback still delivers it to Telegram. Restart the container, and the agent resumes from the stream with no lost messages.

Constraint on 4: the fallback is dead simple — no policy, no batching, raw text to Telegram.

Maintained by the container-service reliability contract from the workload-class map: `restart: unless-stopped`, heartbeat, staleness watched from outside the container. Judgment is maintained as prose files the agent edits under Joel's steering — no config surface to rot.

## Vocabulary

- **gateway agent** — the always-on Claude Fable agent loop in a container service; owns all comms policy in both directions.
- **transport** — the existing gateway daemon reduced to platform mechanics (Chat SDK adapters, single pollers, delivery); zero policy.
- **fallback** — the dead-simple path: when the agent's heartbeat key is absent, transport delivers the producer's text verbatim to one statically configured channel (default Telegram, SMS latent); every fallback delivery is marked in the stream.
- **heartbeat** — a Redis key with TTL the agent refreshes (~15 s refresh, 60 s TTL); transport checks existence per message at ingress — no latch, no fallback mode.
- **kill drill** — the weekly scheduled run of the kill test against the real container and Joel's real DM; the raw ping is the receipt.
- **stream** — the event-sourcing message event log; the agent's only durable memory; the container holds no state that matters.
- **origin record** — producer, machine, herdr pane/session, flowId, appended with every outbound message; makes reply routing mechanical.
- **rewrite** — the gateway authors every operator-facing message in one voice; producers hand over facts, not prose.
- **evidence** — everything a producer sends (text, kind, priority, `--data`); it informs the agent's judgment, it never instructs routing.
- **storm** — a burst of related producer messages; aggregated into one delivery, never twenty pings.
- **revive** — wake-registry SPAWN/REVIVE of a dead origin session, carrying Joel's reply and the original context.

## Notes

Domain: joelclaw messaging (`skills/messaging/SKILL.md`), gateway daemon (`packages/gateway/`), message event stream (`packages/message-event-log/`, effort `message-event-stream`), herdr orchestration, wake registry (`pane-scheduling`), voice agent (`infra/voice-agent/`, `call-joel`).

Skills every session should consult: `messaging`, `herdr-orchestration`, `pane-scheduling`, `effect`. House style binds: XState v5 for lifecycles, Inngest for durable multi-step work, Effect for TypeScript services. Observability doctrine: staleness signals are the killer feature. The five resilience contract clauses bind (boundary-loop doctrine, successor assertions, distributions-over-extremes, aggregate-join ban, unhandled-work receipts) — plus the sixth, binding as of 2026-07-21: hard alerts go through the shared incident-semantics latch (`@joelclaw/incident-latch`). The gateway agent is a hard-alert path; the decision-loop design must ride or deliberately supersede the latch, not duplicate it.

Standing calls (Joel, 2026-07-21, charter grilling):

- LLM in the path of every message. No artificial latency budget.
- Harness: Claude Fable agent loop. Compact context before 250k tokens.
- The agent fans out to herdr-based pi subagents, choosing model and reasoning tier per task.
- Transport stays dumb; the agent owns all policy.
- Steering lives in the agent's own system prompt — its AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md plus gateway Brain and system Brain — always plain ELI5 language written like Joel. The agent edits its own files when told.
- The gateway owns the rewrite and the phone escalation.
- Memory is an event-sourcing style stream.
- Storms are aggregated.
- Full replacement — no shadow window, no staged cutover. The fallback and source-control rollback are the safety story.
- A custom Claude plugin likely packages the gateway loop's tooling (mid-charter, on the plugin-surface question).
- One inbound contract: every event from Joel — free text, reaction, button tap — is the same envelope in the stream, interpreted by the agent. No mechanical fast path (producer-facts grilling).
- The prototype must have a clear iteration path to production if it proves out: real seams (stream replay, plugin packaging, receipt shapes), throwaway glue only at the edges.
- Fallback channel is one static deploy-time config value (`FALLBACK_CHANNEL`), default Telegram; SMS is the most visible surface to Joel and the desired eventual default via the existing Telnyx stack — add after the kill test repeats, then flip the config (fallback grilling).
- The kill test runs as a real weekly drill: kill the production agent container, deliver a real raw message to Joel's DM. No drill flags, no test channels, no mocks (fallback grilling).

Execution is not yet authorized. Steps produce decisions; build authorization lands when [Plan the full cutover](./plan-full-cutover.svx) closes.

## Decision ledger

_(charter settlements live in Finish line, Vocabulary, and Notes)_

- [Map the voice escalation seam](./map-voice-escalation-seam.svx) — keep the existing LiveKit/Telnyx phone stack, but put one correlated adapter in front of it because today's CLI proves a SIP answer, not that the voice worker joined and delivered the reason.
- [Design the producer facts contract](./design-producer-facts-contract.svx) — producers report what happened, the agent decides what Joel hears: all metadata is evidence not instruction, origin auto-stamped + `--data` escape hatch, deprecation rows die, and every inbound event (taps included) rides the same stream envelope through the agent.
- [Map the message event stream seam](./map-stream-seam.svx) — the log kernel is sound, but gateway memory needs typed origin and decision events plus independent paginated replay.
- [Map the herdr and Claude plugin surface](./map-herdr-and-plugin-surface.svx) — package the Fable loop as a Claude plugin over Herdr protocol 17; add a host bridge only if the container socket canary fails.
- [Inventory the transport/policy split](./inventory-transport-policy-split.svx) — keep platform mechanics, normalization, journaling, correlation, delivery, and receipts in transport; move routing, suppression, batching, rewrite, and formatting policy to the gateway agent.
- [Design the fallback contract](./design-fallback-contract.svx) — heartbeat is a Redis TTL key checked per message with no latch; fallback sends producer text verbatim to one statically configured channel (default Telegram, SMS latent); send-then-append `fallback.delivered` marking with recovery reconciliation left to agent judgment; a weekly real-container, real-DM kill drill is the repeatable proof.

## Latent

- Facts-over-prose producer payloads beyond plain text — richer structured handoff once the rewrite proves itself (the contract step covers coexistence; full schema evolution is soft).
- Linux-node migration affinity for the agent container — portable by construction; re-examine at Linux-node time.
- iMessage stays hand-rolled under the transport; modernizing it is not this effort.
- Discord-threads convergence — see Out of scope; Joel marked it "absolutely latent": expected to return as its own successor effort once the gateway earns trust.

## Out of scope

- pi-discord-threads (the interactive Discord steering surface) — different direction of conversation, mid-migration to a system daemon under resilience-engineering; folding it in couples Joel's steering ability to the newest thing in the fleet (Joel, 2026-07-21).
- Rebuilding transport mechanics — Chat SDK adapters, single-poller ownership, and delivery receipts stay as they are.
